    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm using an AZERTY keyboard on Fedora 41.\n\nI'm using LazyVim that bind the key `<C_/>` to open terminal. It works great with Gnome-Terminal, Xterm or even WezTerm.\n\nBut, with kitty, the keybinding acts like I only press `/`. \n\nI thought that was a kitty-terminal problem and reported the bug here https://github.com/kovidgoyal/kitty/issues/8046 (Please disregard the disagreement between the author and me in this conversation.)\nThe author explains that NeoVim probably not interpret the keybinding as it should.\n\nAt this time, and I don't know why, pressing `Ctrl \\` acts like if I press `Ctrl Shift /`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI only installed LazyVim and pressed `Ctrl Shift /` on different terminal emulator\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo have the same mapping on kitty-terminal than with WezTerm or Gnome terminal\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.2 \n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI don't use vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora Linux 41\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.37.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nFedora Packages",
